text: This seems good but seems like it could have been much more. They should of tried to make the toys look just like the originals. A part of their charm is how humble, simple and worn they are and yet kindness shines through. With CGI, they could have brought the stuffed animals to life to see Christopher's imaginary world come to life. Perhaps in the imaginary world his toys could look more vibrant and lively... vs. the real world versions that are drab looking.  This movie is like looking at his life from an adult's perspective. When I think the story deserves something much more special... to be seen through a child's imagination to really capture the essence of Christopher Robin's world.
